Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Friday and welcome back to our 66th Weekly Dose of Optimism.
Packy here for a Weekly Dose first: an essay takeover.=20
First things first, I=E2=80=99m launching a new podcast today, Age of Mirac=
les, along with Julia DeWahl [ https://substack.com/redirect/185304a0-571a-=
4be3-ad68-a806f5ec743f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqO=
sa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] and the incredible Turpentine [ https://substack.com/redir=
ect/54fd4ef2-3152-4056-8ab4-bff244199b34?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_=
ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] team =E2=80=93 Nancy Xu [ https://substa=
ck.com/redirect/9ae1bbe7-cff5-4814-8465-a2d77fa40a7b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ=
=2Egb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8=
ExkRNpU ], Amelia Salyers [ https://su=
bstack.com/redirect/097130d7-f765-434b-ad1a-8c3f0f0cacd1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3=
QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], Tom Hollands [ https://=
substack.com/redirect/35ccf7ad-874b-4c36-b934-dc2083769a5d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], Justin Golden, Jake S=
alyers, and Erik Torenberg [ https://substack.com/redirect/41b3e603-ced0-4f=
e6-a596-de12af55e8fd?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa=
8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=20
It=E2=80=99s more than a dude with a mic talking to other dudes, and we=E2=
=80=99ll get to what it is and why we=E2=80=99re doing it in a second, but =
first, my producers (=F0=9F=92=81=F0=9F=8F=BB=E2=80=8D=E2=99=82=EF=B8=8F) w=
ill kill me if I don=E2=80=99t beg you to listen, like, subscribe, and shar=
e.=20
Today, we=E2=80=99re releasing our first two episodes. You can find them on=
 Apple [ https://substack.com/redirect/5b72759d-e9b1-464b-99bf-7dc851f90cb9=
?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], Spot=
ify [ https://substack.com/redirect/83f61c05-1824-4347-af96-126014d19b4b?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], YouTub=
e, and wherever you listen to podcasts:
We want this to spread outside of tech, so if you like it, I=E2=80=99d real=
ly appreciate it if you shared with a few friends who you think might, too.=
=20
Don=E2=80=99t worry: we=E2=80=99re not going to short you on the optimism. =
Dan dropped five stories at the bottom, and it was a good week for the opti=
mists. My bet is, the weeks are going to keep getting better if we fight to=
 make it happen.=20
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.
Today=E2=80=99s Not Boring (and Age of Miracles) is Sponsored by=E2=80=A6 T=
egus [ https://substack.com/redirect/c6ab2fdb-8bbe-44e5-8c1b-6a28d11f9312?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Imagine a day where every minute of your research is well spent. Where info=
rmation gives you the freedom to be bold. Tegus [ https://substack.com/redi=
rect/c6ab2fdb-8bbe-44e5-8c1b-6a28d11f9312?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA=
_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] is research without all the tedious hun=
ting, calling, parsing, and pasting. You get access to expert calls, custom=
 financial models, and public filing data=E2=80=94 all in one place. The ti=
me for a more powerful perspective is here. Do what you do best, even bette=
r.
Age of Miracles
If you=E2=80=99re reading this, you have the chance to live in an Age of Mi=
racles. Of the 100 billion people who have walked the earth, we=E2=80=99re =
the lucky ones who get to experience the best part. But it=E2=80=99s going =
to take some work.=C2=A0
I want you to close your eyes and imagine with me. Metaphorically, of cours=
e. We don=E2=80=99t have the technology to read with our eyes closed=E2=80=
=A6 yet.=C2=A0
OK, ready?=C2=A0
The year is 2073. It=E2=80=99s a cool spring day, light breeze, 73 degrees.=
